
[1]sounding-board

   SOUND'ING-BOARD, n. A board or structure with a flat surface, suspended
   over a pulpit to prevent the sound of the preacher's voice from
   ascending, and thus propagating it further in a horizontal direction.
   [Used in American churches.]
